<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I couldn't disagree with you more. The spirit of the shaman is protecting the tribe. I remember when I left everfrost on an adventure, I was appalled to see people selling sow. Although, at first, I was tempted, I realized this was totally contrary to my code of ethics. SoW is a power given to us by the gods, to be used to help others. As to the comment, "what if the people we sow hurt others"? All I can say to that, is if we find that our gift was abused, don't give it again. As, with all things, what goes around, comes around. Now in my 51st season, my generosity is paying off 10 fold. Now when people get a shaman item they can't use they think of me and send a tell "dessie can you use such and such". So all things being equal I vote for free SoWs.<p>

I AM NOT A SCAB</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
