<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I am a Shaman in my 52nd season and through most of my career I have sowed for free...  I have made many friends and allies this way, who have stayed with me throughout the game.  I have found that sometimes people who charge for things like sow expect free buffs or heals or clarity or resses.  I suppose by your arguement if you wanted to have a res when you died you would have been a cleric. A sow can save someones life and its only mana. If you want to charge fine but generousity shouldnt be penalized. And who knows, maybe that cleric u sow today will not charge u 200pp to res u when they hit 49 ;).  Think of how many sows ud have to sell... <br>
