<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I sow for free. And buff. And bind. And lead people to places and show them how to get stuff when they have absolutely no clue where to go to get what they want. Why do I do this? Because I can remember being a wee little shammie of 6 seasons on Karana (I currently 40 seasons and play on Lanys). I was poor and struggling. Frustrated. A blessing came along in the form of a elder shammie. She told me she had just attained 39 seasons. She buffed me with all her buffs, and showed me some hunting grounds. She gave me 3 sow potions when they were more expensive to make. Her name starts with a J, but I am ashamed to say I cannot remember the rest. This was over 6 months ago, and I still remember that kindness. Made my day.<p>

Its fun to buff the yahoo out of a little noobie at the gate and watch them go nuts on the bats near FP <img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/Wilk.gif" border="0" align="middle"><p>

Oh yah. My chanter gives out clarity for free as well.<p>

&lt;note: the one time I refused a character a sow came this past week. I'm working on my blacksmithing skill, and a lowbie ranger who conned green to a 20th season, he had anon on so not sure what his actual level is) tried to extort money / sow / buff from those of us attempting to use the forge. He had opened the forge, and was refusing to leave without some form of payment. I do not find this behavior to be honorable, and I'll be hanged before I reward someone for being a jerk. Yes, the three of us waiting did have to get a GM involved. But Diclyn did NOT get his sow&gt;<p>

Brani Spiritblood,<br>
Shaybabe Extraordinaire<br>
Lanys T'vyl</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
