<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">People who beg me repeatedly in a way that leads me to believe that they EXPECT a free SoW don't get one. People who ask me in the middle of a freaking melee (happens more than you'd think) or just after they saw me get my ass beat and ask as soon as I sit down to med/mem don't get one. Ask me very nicely with concern for my current health/mana status and you can have one. Ask me creatively (only had one that left me laughing so far) and I'll probably toss in a buff or two or three, even a weapon or coin if they're nekked or a newbie.<p>

I buff/heal/SoW newbies in my hometown every time I go back to bank or buy spells. Mostly I ask THEM if they need anything. I remember all too well the kind people who helped me out when I was just starting. They wouldn't let me pay them back so I'm passing it on.<p>

On the other hand, hanging out in Oasis and seeing all the twinks running about I can see where one might want to charge. :) I'm thinking about asking all twinks running around on ANONYMOUS to do a /a first. If they're level 15+ they can probably afford a donation.....<p>

Gingivitis, Troll Shaman<br>
