<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Well to begin this my main character cannot sow but I have played characters who can.  And I would have to say that anyone who doesn't sow people without charging them would not be my friend.  I think that is a very selfish way to look at it.  Sure it's annoying when people beg for sow or expect it.  And I have payed for many sows myself.  But I have asked for many without expecting to pay or being expected to.  Sow is a great spell that is nice to have on constantly.  It saves time and allows you to get where you are going faster and have more fun.  Generally I don't pay for sow.  But when there is a situation, (I'm in a hurry or going somewhere dangerous or when I have a few people who need sow) I'll usually pay 5plat to the sower.  And as a general rule you don't ask while they are fighting.  I almost never ask a shaman who is soloing since mana is what is determining when they can go into their next fight.  But you also have to remember once you get into the 20's sow takes almost no mana.  And if you're nice and offer your services people will be nice and return the favor when you need it.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
