<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">First off i want to say that calling those who give out SoW free scabs is wrong.  Shaman are supposed to be the enlightened ones amoung the less educated.  We are the ones with the BRAINS!  We are also healers and are supposed to be the ones taking care of the others that aren't "gifted" with the powers to heal (that is if you Roleplay)  So giving a SoW, Healing, Buffing all of these are your job as a healer.  Now some people are ridiculous in the way they beg and beg for heals buffs and sows but you need to use your own judgment when deciding whether to help someone.  I usually sow and buff for free and sometimes i get donations i dont even ask for sometime there a hell of alot more than what i would have gotten if i charged for one.  One time i gave a DarkElf a sow in W Karana and he gave me a pair of Bronze Greaves for it which i later sold for 20pp (which isnt bad money for a low lvl shaman) now to me that made up for all the free sows i gave away plus it helps in letting people know that your not stingy with your mana and will help out when you can and that of course gets your name out there when groups are forming.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
