<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Greetings again,<p>

I have revised my feeling on sowing people here. When I was younger, I did take donations for sow and I did get paid well. Now, I am in my 30th season and sow is always free. I have not charged people for a sow since I was 15 and likely never will. I also do not charge for buffs for the most part. At my level, the mana is negligible, due to specialization in Alteration and it never fizzles, so I routinely do shouts for free sows at FP gates, Qeynos, whatever.<p>

As I have grown older, I am running into many trade offs instead. I typically get requests from chanters for "sow for breeze", clerics for "sow for buffs" or the usual sow for CR reaquests. For me now, I sow freely and never ask for anything for it. I notice that at my level, if I need money, I will go hunt giants. Why charge for something that I am blessed with? A scab huh? Maybe in your eyes, but when I go to my hunt zones, the reaction is far different when I shout for a group. I am usually greeted with at least 5 tells in a row becuase people know of me and that I routinely help others. If you want to think of this as being a scab, then so be it. But this type of attitude will show up later in the game when people stop wanting to group because of being extorted for money. You have a gift. You do not have to share it, but when you do, you share more than the sow, you share your name and people will remember.<p>

Peace...<p>

Wordaen out</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
