<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">This is my first time playing a Shaman.  Have played Warriors, Necromancer, Wizard and a Rouge.  I remember how nice it was that people would give sow for free.  I find great pleasure and a little bit of wicked amusement out of doing "random drive by buffs and sow's" of both newbies and experienced players alike.  Especially when I have SOW running on myself...run up....buff buff...run away....the bewildered reaction of why you did that for free is worth the effort.  You get some funny reactions when people actually have to scroll back to find out what happened and the send you a tell.  The only thing I have ever asked in return was that someday when they are high enough level to help out a newbie or someone less experienced that they do the same.<p>

Grimfall<br>
Random Acts (of Kindness)<br>
