<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">*chuckles*<p>

I have sowed and buffed for free most of my shaman life. Rarely do I even accept donations, unless the timing of the person asking is inconvenient.  Sometimes, however, the expectations of others can be down right aggravating. My most memorable account was a hunt that was taking place in Runnyeye.  I was but a wee lass of late teens.  Our group had taken much damage, and several lost their lives, I included.  I was trying to make my way down to my corpse, without much success. Racing back to the Beholder zone, I stepped through clinging to the last remenants of life (about 4 hps), with no mana, and still naked. Just as I popped into Beholder, a gent looks at me and asks for sow and buffs. My response:<p>

/emote looks down at her naked and beaten body.<p>

/emote peers at (so and so).<p>

Um, a moment. I dun 'ave any mana.<p>

His response:<p>

Ok, I'll wait.<p>

Did he pay? No. Did I ask for payment? No. Am I crazy? Probably.<hr>Jilie Mackintosh<br>
42 Shaman<br>
Bristlebane</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
